Company description:



Choosing Capgemini means choosing a company where you will be empowered to shape your career in the way you'd like, where you'll be supported and inspired by‚ÄØa collaborative community of colleagues around the world, and where you'll be able to reimagine what's possible. Job description:



Your Role

To lead and support the implementation, monitoring, and continuous improvement of AML Policy and Standard. This role ensures the bank operates within its zero-tolerance risk appetite for Money laundering, terrorist financing, bribery and corruption, maintaining compliance with legal and regulatory obligations across all jurisdictions.

In this role you will play a key role in:

Oversee the application of AML Policy across all business units and subsidiaries.
Conduct risk assessments and due diligence on Business Partners, suppliers, and third-party agents
Investigate and report suspected breaches, ensuring appropriate escalation and resolution.
Collaborate with Strategic Sourcing and Legal teams to assess vendor compliance.
Maintain accurate records of compliance activities and risk mitigation efforts.
Support the development and review of related policies (e.g., AML/CTF, Fraud Control, Whistleblower).
Report to the Group Operational Risk Committee and Board Risk Committee as required.


Profile description:



Your Profile

Bachelor's degree in Law, Finance, Risk, or related field.
5+ years in compliance, risk management, or regulatory affairs.
Strong understanding of anti-bribery, corruption, and AML/CTF legislation.
Experience in policy implementation and stakeholder engagement.
Excellent analytical, communication, and investigative skills.


We offer:



What you'll love about working here



Experience a Positive Work-Life Balance: We prioritize your well-being with hybrid and flexible working arrangements, making it easy to balance your personal and professional life.
Own your Growth: Dive into endless learning opportunities with courses from Capgemini University and numerous external certifications. Benefit from digital learning platforms and specialized campuses in AI, Cloud, Data, and Sustainability. Propel your career with our award-winning Career Acceleration programs.
Thrive in an Inclusive Environment: We don't just believe in inclusion; we live it. Bring your authentic self to work in a safe, flexible, and welcoming environment, supported by staff-led community groups and active allyship.
Work with Integrity: Join a company recognized by Ethisphere as one of the World's most Ethical companies.
Collaborate with Industry Leaders: Gain exposure to top global companies, including 145 of the Fortune 500, through your work with Capgemini.
Showcase Your Skills: Participate in our internal annual global tech challenges and help address world issues.

Company description:



The Metcash story began from the humble origins of our first family-owned corner store in 1927. And for almost 100 years since then, we've been backing independents and strengthening the communities we operate in.

Today, Metcash (ASX: MTS) is Australia and New Zealand's leading independent retail partner and wholesaler in the food, liquor, hardware, and tools industries, with sales of $19.5 billion in FY25. We provide our network with marketing, purchasing, warehousing, distribution and systems support



Job description:



At Metcash, you're part of something bigger. We've got the heart of a small business with the strength and support of a big business. When you join Metcash, your work makes a real difference to independent businesses and local communities, empowering you to:

Grow your career with tailored development programs
Make your mark in a high-performing, values-led team
Thrive your way with flexible work options

About the Opportunity

At Metcash, we believe that data should do more than sit in a warehouse‚Äîit should power decisions, shape customer experiences, and help our retailers and suppliers thrive. That's where you come in.

We're looking for an Analytics Engineer to join our Enterprise Data & Analytics team (EDAA). This is your chance to design, build and operate enterprise-grade Power BI solutions that turn data into actionable insight for thousands of businesses across Australia.

This is a 12 months fixed-term role.

In this Role, You Will:

Design, build and maintain end-to-end BI solutions: semantic models, Power BI datasets, dataflows, dashboards and deployment pipelines.
Translate business needs into clean, reusable data models and self-service analytics layers.
Engineer high-performance solutions using DAX, M and advanced optimisation tools.
Partner with data engineers to define modern ingestion and transformation patterns (ADF/Synapse/Fabric).
Ensure accuracy, governance and security (RLS/OLS) across enterprise datasets.
Champion UI/UX excellence‚Äîfrom intuitive navigation to on-brand visual standards.
Leverage AI-assisted features to accelerate development, insight generation and storytelling.
(Senior level) Mentor teammates, set best practice standards, and lead initiatives spanning multiple domains.

You're Likely a Match If You Have:

Hands-on expertise in Power BI (DAX, Power Query/M) and strong SQL skills.
A solid grasp of dimensional modelling, star schemas, and data warehouse design.
Experience integrating with Azure Data Factory, Synapse or Fabric; knowledge of CI/CD pipelines (e.g., Git, Azure DevOps).
Strong problem-solving skills‚Äîable to translate complex business challenges into elegant technical solutions.
A portfolio of impactful, enterprise-ready BI solutions.
(Bonus) Microsoft certifications in Power BI or Azure Data/Analytics.

About Us

Metcash is Australia's leading wholesale distribution company, with $19.5 billion in sales (FY25) and a proud spot in the ASX Top 125. We believe in the power of independent, family-owned businesses to shape vibrant communities. Through our food, liquor, and hardware pillars, we help retailers become the ‚ÄòBest Store in Their Town' by providing merchandising, operational and marketing support.
We're committed to diversity, inclusion, and sustainability ‚Äî and we welcome applicants from all backgrounds, including First Nations. If you need support during the application process, just let us know. Your privacy and dignity are always respected.



Join us and be part of something bigger!

Shape the future of property, investment & beyond with one of Australia‚Äôs most respected family-owned businesses.

For more than 60 years, the Dennis Family Group has been at the forefront of Australian property. Through our diverse businesses ‚Äî from residential land development (Dennis Family Corporation), to commercial real estate (Ranfurlie Asset Management), farming, and private investments ‚Äî we‚Äôve built a reputation for stability, growth, and success.

Now, we‚Äôre looking for a Financial Analyst to join our Corporate Finance team and play a key role in driving strategic decisions across this exciting mix of industries.

¬†

About the Role

As a Financial Analyst, you‚Äôll provide the insight and analysis that helps shape significant decisions. From evaluating new investments to strengthening financial reporting and supporting capital allocation, your work will influence the Group‚Äôs growth and performance.

This is a highly visible role working with senior leaders and Boards, giving you the opportunity to make an impact across all parts of the Group.

Key responsibilities include:

Financial modelling, valuations, scenario analysis & investment reviews

Supporting new investment proposals and strategic capital decisions

Group-wide cash flow forecasting, planning & reporting

Partnering with business units to provide performance insights

Preparing financial reports & presentations for management and Boards

¬†

4+ years‚Äô experience in corporate finance, investment, property development, M&A, or professional services (deal/due diligence teams ideal)

Strong financial modelling, valuation & analysis skills

Advanced Excel & financial systems capability

Clear communicator with the ability to influence stakeholders

¬†

Why Join Us? The Dennis Family Difference

We believe our people are part of our extended family ‚Äî and we back that up with benefits that matter:

Long-term stability with a successful, multi-generational Australian-owned business

Hybrid working (2 days from home per week)

Responsibilities
Unique opportunity with Aon‚Äôs Reinsurance team to support the comprehensive approach to risk assessment, risk transfer and risk mitigation
Effective catastrophe management is an essential component of an insurer‚Äôs risk management program.
Open to applicants Australia wide, Aon offers flexible working

¬†

Aon is in the business of better decisions

At Aon, we shape decisions for the better to protect and enrich the lives of people around the world.

As an organization, we are united through trust as one inclusive team and we are passionate about helping our colleagues and clients succeed.

¬†

What the day will look like

Using significant expertise of all major catastrophe models, our analysts overcome data and model limitations to provide clients with a comprehensive view of their portfolio. The team is in regular dialogue with all major modelling firms and provides clients with detailed explanations for model changes and interpreting their potential effect on results.

Key responsibilities include - ¬†

Utilising catastrophe modelling software to determine clients‚Äô exposure to catastrophe hazards such as earthquake, cyclone and bushfire;
Refining catastrophe models and outputs by analysing clients‚Äô historical data and latest scientific research.
Interrogating client exposure and claim data in MS Excel or SQL to support analyses;
Translating complex technical findings into clear insights and recommendations for internal and external stakeholders
Developing effective working relationships with internal and external clients; and
Actively contributing to climate and natural perils advisory projects.

¬†

How this opportunity is different

Work at the intersection of the science, risk and business with a direct impact on the management of natural hazards for our clients in Australia and New Zealand.

Together with our actuaries and brokers, our catastrophe team helps clients navigate the challenges of natural peril risk. This includes support for client reinsurance placements and optimising risk transfer strategies, plus on-going research into climate trends and catastrophe model adjustments.

¬†

¬†Skills and experience that will lead to success

The ability to work well within a team, a curious mindset and strong problem-solving and analytical skills
Tertiary qualifications in relevant field of study ‚Äì natural sciences, engineering, mathematics or statistics
Knowledge of catastrophe modelling software (preferred)
Advanced Excel skills and strong a working knowledge of MS Word, SQL and PowerPoint
Comfortable in client-facing, collaborative, consulting environment with excellent communication skills (both oral and written)
Insurance or reinsurance experience
Experience with VBA, Python, R, Tableau/PowerBI or AI tools an advantage but not essential
Excellent organisation skills and ability to work under pressure
Self-discipline to manage own workflow and deadlines¬†

How we support our colleagues

In addition to our comprehensive benefits package, we encourage an inclusive workforce. Plus, our agile environment allows you to manage your wellbeing and work/life balance, ensuring you can be your best self at Aon. Furthermore, all colleagues enjoy two ‚ÄúGlobal Wellbeing Days‚Äù each year, encouraging you to take time to focus on yourself.¬† We offer a variety of working style solutions for our colleagues as well.¬†

¬†

Our continuous learning culture inspires and equips you to learn, share and grow, helping you achieve your fullest potential. As a result, at Aon, you are more connected, more relevant, and more valued.

¬†

The Opportunity

At APA, our purpose is to secure Australia's energy future. We're not doing it alone. We're doing it with our customers and communities as Australia's energy infrastructure partner, a role our unique experience and expertise positions us to play.

We now have an exciting opportunity available for an Operations Analytics and Insights Lead to join our Operations team in either Melbourne, Sydney, Brisbane or Perth, on a full-time permanent basis.

Reporting to the Head of Operations Strategy & Capital, you will be responsible for bringing data-driven insights and analysis to APA's strategic initiatives and plans across Operations including gas infrastructure and power generation asset systems.

Key Responsibilities

Provide advanced analysis and insights supporting Operations' strategy, performance, budgeting and capital prioritisation and governance functions including forecasts, reports and visualisations
Provide cross-functional collaboration, strategic input and guidance to the Operations data, systems and intelligence and technology teams, to ensure alignment with broader Operations strategic needs
Support the development of asset system strategic plans, aligned with APA's long-term goals and objectives, embedding analytics into decision-making and business planning
Translate complex data into clear, actionable insights for senior leadership and communicate clearly and efficiently at all levels in the organisation
Drive continuous improvement and innovation in analytics, identifying improvement opportunities and focusing on efficiency and automation

Your background

Tertiary qualifications in data science, business, economics, engineering or a related relevant field
Able to work independently, identify needs and opportunities, establish relationships and execute plans in collaboration with a wide range of stakeholders
Demonstrated experience in senior business analytics position including development of analytics and insights capability in an operational context
Experience in energy infrastructure operations in Australia, such as gas production, transmission and storage, gas-fired power generation, renewable generation and storage and electricity transmission
Proficient in analytics, database tools, business intelligence and visualisation

Working at APA

At APA we're committed to fostering a safe and inclusive workplace where you can achieve your best. We'll provide you with access to targeted career development programs, competitive remuneration, employee benefits, flexible working arrangements, and wellbeing programs. We also have an inclusive parental leave policy providing 18 weeks leave including superannuation to support parents at work and in life.

We employ more than 2700 people across Australia and are committed to creating a diverse and inclusive culture, where everyone feels safe, valued, and trusted to do their best every day.

We are APA

APA Group is a leading Australian energy infrastructure business.

We proudly own, operate and manage a diverse $26 billion portfolio of gas, electricity, solar and wind assets which deliver essential services to communities and customers across Australia.

And we own more than 15,000 kilometres of gas pipelines which deliver energy to households and businesses across every corner of Australia.

As the partner of choice in delivering infrastructure solutions for the energy transition, we're focused on bundled remote grid energy solutions, electricity and gas transmission, and future energy, including hydrogen and carbon capture and storage.

Our customer centric approach means we understand our customers and offer them reliable, innovative, and cost-effective energy solutions that support their decarbonisation ambitions.

We are committed securing Australia's energy future by delivering infrastructure solutions for Australia's energy transition and supporting the decarbonisation ambitions of our customers and communities .

Join our team and be part of securing Australia's energy future.

We'd love to hear from you.

APA is an equal opportunity employer. The safety, health and wellbeing our people, community and environment a priority. We embrace diversity in our people to ensure our workforce is representative of the communities that we operate in.


Applicants must be eligible to work in Australia to be considered.

This vacancy works with critical APA data, systems or infrastructure and candidates are subject to background vetting (including Police checks) before & during employment.

Role closes 5th of October 2025. Role Reference number JR3270.

APA Group will not accept unsolicited resumes from recruitment agencies.

We will contact successful candidates after the closing date.

Job Title: Finance Analyst | $150k package + bonus | Energy Sector
Ad Text:
Work closely with senior executives in a broad operationally focused role
CBD fringe close to public transport | Up to $150,000 package + bonus
Suited to someone with strong Power BI skills who is interested in energy
The Opportunity

Excellent opportunity to join a growing privately owned business in the energy sector. The Finance Analyst sits within the tightknit finance team and takes on broad responsibilities across financial analysis and modelling, financial accounting, and power BI reporting.¬†
¬†¬†
The Challenge

Reporting to Financial Controller, some of your responsibilities will include:

Reviewing and analysing profit and loss and balance sheet positions prior to the monthly close
Deliver operational reporting to support all departments, identifying and providing insight on cost, productivity and trends.
Recommend changes to processes and systems based on data analysis findings to enhance efficiency and effectiveness.
Build capability in each department to enable reporting tools to be utilised in a self-service manner.
Support budgeting, forecasting, and strategic planning processes.
The Expertise

Please consider expressing interest in this position if you possess the following:

CA/CPA qualification with strong appetite for growth with an interest in the energy sector¬†
Sound technical accounting knowledge, ideally gained within a reputable chartered firm (Audit, Assurance or CFO Advisory)
Highly proficient with Excel-based modelling and Power BI reporting.¬†
Strong communication skills and a team player
The Next Step¬†

If this position will enhance your career and you would like further details on the client, the role, remuneration or a copy of the position description, please call Thomas Burt for a confidential discussion on 0427 465 934¬†
Or alternatively please apply per the link below.

We‚Äôre looking for a highly analytical and driven Technical Business Analyst to join a fast-growing SaaS business as part of a strategic partnership with one of Australia‚Äôs leading banks.

This is a rare opportunity to shape the design and delivery of next-generation financial workflows across onboarding, payments, reconciliation, and fee modelling.

You‚Äôll partner closely with cross-functional teams (Product, Engineering, UI/UX, Finance, Implementations) and be a key counterpart to senior bank stakeholders to streamline and scale critical processes.

What you‚Äôll be doing
Lead structured discovery with internal teams and bank stakeholders to define and prioritise requirements.
Map current- and future-state processes (onboarding, payments, settlements, reconciliations) and design controls.
Build and maintain pricing/fee models to support product, finance, and operational decisions.
Analyse transaction and exception data; recommend levers to improve success rates and reduce manual touchpoints.
Produce high-quality BRDs/PRDs, interface/API specs, and test cases to enable clear, fast delivery.
Support backlog grooming, define UAT strategy, run testing, and guide new features through to go-live.
Provide crisp updates and executive summaries for senior stakeholders.
What we‚Äôre looking for
4‚Äì7+ years‚Äô experience as a Business Analyst, Product Analyst, or Operations Analyst in payments, banking, fintech, or SaaS.
Strong process modelling (BPMN/UML), requirements engineering, and data analysis skills.
Advanced Excel, intermediate+ SQL, and Power BI experience (Python/R is a plus).
Hands-on experience with reconciliation & settlement workflows and direct debit operations.
Familiarity with Australian payment rails (BECS, NPP/Osko, BPAY, cards) preferred.
Excellent stakeholder management, analytical thinking, and structured communication skills.
Why join
Be part of a collaborative, pragmatic, and outcome-driven team.

Join a high performing team contributing to the RBA's role in financial stability

Build your analytical skills and understanding of risks in the global financial system, in an environment invested in your professional development

Permanent opportunity with hybrid working arrangements

Your team

A stable financial system is crucial to the welfare of the Australian people. Financial Stability Department advises the RBA Governors, Board and Council of Financial Regulators on risks to the stability of the financial system and produces the Financial Stability Review.

You will join the Policy & International (P&I) team, which works to enhance the RBA's understanding of financial stability risks and lessons from overseas, contributes to the international policy debate, and leads the development and maintenance of frameworks for financial stability policy advice and analysis. In a rapidly evolving international landscape, the team leverages insights from advanced overseas economies and international policy to inform domestic policy and the assessment of financial stability in Australia.

Your role

You will play a key role in the RBA's work to contribute to financial stability. You will lead and collaborate on projects supporting the RBA's work on financial stability, work closely with your manager to shape your team's work program, and coach more junior staff as appropriate. You will also help deliver high-quality policy advice to the Bank's executive and the Board, which is especially important during stress events overseas and as the lessons are drawn afterwards.

Working in P&I offers an opportunity to develop a deep understanding of risks in the international financial system, and to play a part in bringing insight from the international context to domestic analysis. You will have opportunities to use and develop your strong analytical skills, while answering fascinating questions that help shape our assessment and policy. You will also work closely with other sections within the Department, other areas across the Bank and other government agencies.

Your role will include:

analysing and interpreting a broad array of data and information to develop insights on the links between different parts of the global financial system

identifying and assessing systemic risks and vulnerabilities in the global financial system, while monitoring possible spillovers to financial stability in Australia

briefing the RBA's senior executive, including to support the RBA's contribution to the work of international regulatory bodies

undertaking analysis and providing advice on how climate change and the energy transition might affect the global financial system

developing your thought leadership and problem-solving skills.

Your background

We are looking for a motivated and engaged analyst at a senior or lead level of experience, with a strong interest in policy-relevant work in a collaborative environment. To be successful in the role, you will have:


Strong critical thinking and technical skills, including experience in data analysis.

The ability to work effectively in a team, collaborate productively with a broad range of stakeholders, and to work independently as required.

Strong communication skills, including the ability to prepare clear and concise reports and presentations.

A degree in Economics, Finance, or a related field, preferably an honours degree or higher.

Previous experience in the monitoring and analysis of economic and or financial system developments - and the ability to apply this to climate-related issues - is desirable, but not a prerequisite for the role.

Be More

Working for an organisation that truly makes a difference to the people of Australia, we can offer development and career opportunities in a collaborative environment that supports your growth, wellbeing and promotes flexibility. Your individual growth and success drives the RBA forward as an organisation. Be more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.

Why RBA?

The RBA makes an important contribution to the Australian economy through the pursuit of national economic policy objectives and associated activities in financial markets and banking. We also issue Australia's banknotes and operate infrastructure critical to the payments system, all of which contribute to the welfare of the Australian people. Made up of specialists across a wide range of fields, our people, values, and culture play a critical role in achieving our objectives. Striving to be Open & Dynamic, we consider and incorporate different perspectives, work across teams and are transparent with each other, whilst delivering quality together effectively and focusing on outcomes by prioritising, testing, learning, and refining as we go.

Our people conduct themselves with a high degree of integrity, while striving for excellence in the work they perform and the outcomes they achieve. We encourage intelligent inquiry and we treat one another with respect while promoting the public interest through our efforts. We know it is the growth and success of our people that drives the RBA forward. Come and make a bigger contribution while you build and develop your own skills too, because being more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.

Ad Text:
Our client is seeking a highly skilled Principal Engineer with deep expertise in Data Engineering and Test Data Management (TDM) to join their enterprise technology team. Responsibilities

Collaborate with cross-functional teams (architecture, DevOps, QA, business) to align data engineering and TDM solutions with organizational objectives.

Mentor and guide engineering teams, fostering a culture of continuous improvement, innovation, and knowledge sharing.

Evaluate and introduce emerging technologies, tools, and methodologies that enhance the scalability, automation, and efficiency of data engineering and TDM capabilities.

Act as a trusted advisor to senior leadership, providing strategic input on data strategy, technology roadmaps, and architectural decisions.

Requirements

10+ years of experience in data engineering, with proven experience leading enterprise-scale data initiatives.

Prior background in financial services, banking - A MUST.

Strong expertise in cloud data platforms (Azure, AWS, or GCP) and modern data technologies such as Databricks, Snowflake, Spark, Synapse, Redshift, BigQuery, Kafka.

Hands-on experience with Test Data Management tools (e.g., Delphix, Informatica TDM, GenRocket, IBM InfoSphere Optim) and techniques (masking, synthetic generation, subsetting).

Deep understanding of data modeling, data warehousing, ETL/ELT frameworks, and data integration patterns.

Solid knowledge of data governance, data privacy, and regulatory compliance frameworks.

Proven experience in architecting and scaling enterprise data platforms, including CI/CD integration and automation.

Strong leadership, communication, and stakeholder management skills with the ability to influence at senior levels.

Help people create their tomorrow, while you create yours

We help people with their banking, super, retirement and finances. Through upturns, downturns, recessions, and major life transitions. Every day, we help people see and make more of their financial potential, so that they can create their tomorrow. And we've been doing it for over 175 years.

How will you make an impact

This role is instrumental in advancing AMP's data-driven marketing capabilities through the development and application of advanced analytics, predictive models, and statistical techniques.

By uncovering deeper insights and future trends from complex customer, campaign, and business data, this role enables AMP to deliver more personalised, effective, and measurable marketing strategies across business units. The role also brings innovation to the marketing analytics function, introducing new methodologies and automation to drive continuous improvement and competitive advantage.

Familiarity with data privacy, security, and governance requirements in a regulated environment


Experience working collaboratively with cross-functional teams, including marketing, product, and technology



Why we think you'll love working at AMP

Doing what we've always done is not an option, so your clever ideas will get airtime here. You'll be encouraged to speak up and try new things. If they don't work, we move on - better for it.

We know there's no one way of doing things. So, you won't have to sacrifice who you are or how you work to fit in here. We're inclusive and flexible in many of the ways you'd expect. And in some of the ways you wouldn't. As long as your health and wellbeing come first - at home and at work.

In fact, most of what makes AMP such a welcoming, enjoyable place to work are our people. Wherever you go, you'll find moments to connect, feel valued and do meaningful work.

Whether it's through our first-class leaders who are invested in you and your success. Through year-round opportunities to volunteer, fundraise and give back to the community. Or in the everyday challenges you face as we work together to strengthen this great organisation. Challenges that will stretch you, amplify your potential and compound the impact you have.



We believe in the power of inclusion and diversity

We're dedicated to fostering inclusion, diversity, and a warm feeling of belonging at AMP. It sparks creativity, ignites innovation, and turns up the dial on the quality of our decisions and performance. This not only makes our workplace more engaged but also leads to better connections with our customers.

We're your allies in the search for the perfect fit - when you apply, let us know how we can support you to put your best self forward during our selection process.

We're also committed to enhancing employment opportunities for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, so we enthusiastically encourage candidates from these backgrounds to apply and explore our Reconciliation Plan on our website.



Ready to create your tomorrow?

If you're someone who sees opportunity where others see challenge, come and work with us in smart, progressive ways as we transform an iconic Australian brand for the future. And, through a series of career-defining moments, create your own tomorrow.

Don't procrastinate! We review applications when we get them, and if we discover the ideal candidate, we may close the role earlier than the advertised close date.

Looking forward to meeting you.
